</style>

<div class="header">
  <div class="header-content">
    <div class="tag">Compiled by Gemini 3.1</div>
    <h1>Southern Company (SO)<br/>Intrinsic Value</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">A transparent, two-stage discounted cash flow valuation of Southern Company using actual financials and Operating Cash Flow proxy.</p>
    <p class="date">Updated {new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { month: 'long', day: 'numeric', year: 'numeric' })}</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
  <!-- ═══ THE VERDICT ═══ -->
  <div class="verdict-card">
    <div class="verdict-label">Estimated Intrinsic Value Per Share</div>
    <div class="verdict-price">${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}</div>
    <div class="verdict-vs">vs. market price of ${currentMarketPrice.toFixed(2)} ({marginOfSafety}%)</div>
    <div class="verdict-badge" style={`background: ${verdictColor}22; color: ${verdictColor}; border: 1px solid ${verdictColor}44;`}>
      {verdictText}
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ KEY METRICS ═══ -->
  <div class="stats-row">
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{revenue[0] !== null ? `$${(revenue[0] / 1000).toFixed(1)}B` : 'N/A'}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">TTM Revenue</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{baseOCF > 0 ? `$${(baseOCF / 1000).toFixed(1)}B` : 'N/A'}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Operating Cash Flow</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{eps[0] !== null ? `$${eps[0].toFixed(2)}` : 'N/A'}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">EPS (Diluted)</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{revenue[0] !== null && operatingIncome[0] !== null ? `${((operatingIncome[0] / revenue[0]) * 100).toFixed(1)}%` : 'N/A'}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Operating Margin</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{netCash !== null ? `$${(netCash / 1000).toFixed(1)}B` : 'N/A'}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Net Cash</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ METHODOLOGY ═══ -->
  <h2>Methodology: Two-Stage DCF</h2>
  <p>We use a <strong>two-stage discounted cash flow (DCF)</strong> model. For utilities with massive capital expenditures, standard Free Cash Flow is often consistently negative. Thus, we base our valuation on Operating Cash Flow (OCF), proxying the core business cash generation.</p>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">1</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Start with actual Operating Cash Flow</h4>
      <p>Southern Company generated <strong>${baseOCF > 0 ? (baseOCF / 1000).toFixed(2) : 0} billion</strong> in operating cash flow recently. We use this as the proxy base because raw FCF is distorted by intensive infrastructure CapEx.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">2</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Project OCF growth for 5 years (Phase 1)</h4>
      <p>We grow OCF at <strong>{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(2)}%</strong> per year for 5 years, derived mathematically from its recent CAGR and constrained by broader market rates.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">3</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Calculate terminal value (Phase 2)</h4>
      <p>After Year 5, we assume growth settles at <strong>{(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(2)}%</strong> (Gordon Growth Model), derived from a fraction of the 10Y Treasury yield, fitting for a mature regulated utility.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">4</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Discount everything to present value</h4>
      <p>Cash flows are discounted at <strong>{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(2)}%</strong>. This required rate of return proxy is strictly mathematically derived as 1.5x the 10Y Treasury yield of {(tenYearTreasury * 100).toFixed(2)}%.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">5</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Add net cash, divide by shares</h4>
      <p>We add the net debt position (Cash minus Debt) to the Enterprise Value, dividing by total diluted shares outstanding to reach the intrinsic value.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ THE THREE ASSUMPTIONS ═══ -->
  <h2>The Three Assumptions That Drive Everything</h2>

  <div class="assumption-grid">
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">OCF Growth Rate (Years 1-5)</div>
      <div class="value">{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(2)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Derived mathematically from historical Operating Cash Flow compound annual growth rate, representing expected core operational growth for the utility.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Discount Rate (Proxy WACC)</div>
      <div class="value">{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(2)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Derived mathematically as 1.5× the current 10Y Treasury yield ({(tenYearTreasury * 100).toFixed(2)}%). A utility presents stable cash flow, necessitating a moderate risk premium.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Terminal Growth Rate</div>
      <div class="value">{(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(2)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Derived as 0.5× the 10Y Treasury yield. Regulated utilities generally track closely with population and long-term conservative GDP growth.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ OCF PROJECTIONS TABLE ═══ -->
  <h2>Projected Cash Flows</h2>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="text-align:left">Year</th>
